description:
As Shuichi decides to debut in the US with XMR records, his relationships with Eiri and Reiji reach an impasse. Shuichi breaks the news to Eiri that he wants to forget about his life in Japan...including Eiri!

Track 37 - 41.
name: Vol. 9

description:
Shuichi returns to Japan and to his surprise, Eiri has come to greet him at the airport. Shuichi reveals that he just wants Eiri to open up to him. Hearing this, Eiri offers to say "I love you"...if Shuichi agrees to pay him every time he says it. Although Eiri is joking, Shuichi is dead serious about raising the money to hear those precious words. However, Eiri says something else that will leave Shuichi so shocked he will be unable to sing!

Track 42 - 45 & bonus track.
name: Vol. 10

description:
When it rains, it pours... Shuichi keeps digging himself deeper into the hole--the plans to release 5 singles in 3 weeks have been bumped up to 10 singles!! Talk about working hard for the money--Shuichi's responsible for 80% of the work for their upcoming, super-ambitious release schedule! Can Shuichi withstand the pressure, or will he crumble? Everyone's watching Bad Luck--can this band get down to business, or will time run out on the countdown?

Track 46 - 48 & Gravitation track 13651.
name: Vol. 11

description: Bad Luck is out to crash Nittle Grasper's concert with a brand new song! Can Shuichi steal the thunder from Ryuichi, or has Bad Luck's streak finally run out? At the same time, Shuichi and Yuki's relationship has hit the roof--will the shadow of a former love bring down the curtain for good? Don't miss this rocking finale!
name: Vol. 12

description: So far, AC Comics ONLY true foray into crime comics. "Only those that embrace me shall see me and those that embrace me shall suffer... for I am a tool of the Devil... I am Lady Crime." Horror hosts like E.C."s Crypt Keeper, or Warren Publication's Uncle Creepy are familiar enough, in the late-1940's heyday of crime comics, similar narrative characters were used in those books, too. Charles Biro's "Mr. Crime", from Crime Does Not Pay, being the most memorable. When the great Bob Powell jumped on the crime comics gravy train of that era, leave it to him to provide the concept with a superb sense of irony- a beautiful woman as the ultimate spirit of evil! And so Lady Crime was born. Unfortuneately for Powell fans, the Lady only appeared a couple of times in the Golden Age, and one of those appearances is reprinted in this book, "Murder For Pennies", originally seen in Kerry Drake Comics #8, May of 1948. AC's editorial staff took the liberty of utilizing the talents of Lady Crime to narrate two other wild, Powell- drawn precode crime stories here, though;"Aristocrat Of Crime",first printed in Fawcett's Down With Crime, circa 1950; and "Underground Oblivian". Plus, another two-page Powell featurette- "How Good A detective Are You?"

Basil Wolverton's enigmatic, mysterious man from outer space is back! Can even Spacehawk survive the machinations of Queen Haba of Neptune? Join the scourge of the spaceways as he fights the forces of evil! Story, interior art, and painted cover all by Basil Wolverton.
Join our fierce avenger as he protects the innocent and punishes the guilty! Basil Wolverton's mysterious stranger uses super-science and powerful abilities to make the spaceways safe for all!

Young Barney Gibson wanted to do his bit in World War II, joining the army as a gunner.
An orphan, Barney had always been a bit of a loner as a lad. Now, for the first time, he felt a sense of belonging — his new mates were the closest thing he had ever had to a family.
Then one sudden, vicious attack by German Junkers Ju87 dive-bombers — the dreaded Stukas — took all that away. Barney would never be the same again…
name: Smash All Stukas!

description:
Mountain climbers are a hardy bunch. They have to be for the mountains can be as vicious an unforgiving an enemy as any human foe. Knowing that, they will help fellow climbers even at the risk of their own lives.
Tough as nails mountaineer Hans Kopfler was one such. A member of Germany’s elite Gebirgsjager he had total loyalty to those he served with. Unfortunately that loyalty would not always be shown in the other direction...
name: Climb For Your Life!

description:
“Double-crossed!”…those chilling words seared in to the brain of Dave Gregory, a captain in the Special Boat Service, when a searchlight on a Russian minesweeper picked him out of the inky Baltic night.
For now he might be helpless, his Browning automatic no match for the Russian fire-power, but heaven help the man who had betrayed him when Dave decided it was time to even the scores…
name: Deadly Double-Cross

description:
Deserters, bandits, common thieves — they had all banded together under a powerful leader to wage their own war on all-comers — for profit. Now war correspondent Matt Jarvis, never one to dodge a dangerous assignment, had fallen into their hands.
Just surviving was about to become more important than writing any story!
name: Renegade Army

description:
Story Titles

  • As My Master Wishes... by Michele & Eric Wright
  • Denial On The Nile by Sara "Caribou" Palmer
  • There Is Only One Thing To Do... by Diana Harlan-Stein & David M. Stein
  • Sobek's Just Desserts by Dark Natasha & Thomas G. Brady
  • Out of the Storm by Heather Bruton & Will A. Samborn
  • Avatar Games by Terrie Smith & Glen Wooten

Collects the Superman and the Legion of Super-Heroes story arc consisting of Action Comics # 858 - # 863.

Superstar Gary Frank joins writer Geoff Johns for a epic story teaming Superman with an adult version of the Legion of Super-Heroes. When he was a boy, Clark Kent was isolated and alone until he met this teen team from the 31st Century. Today, it's been years since Superman saw his childhood friends. Why haven't they returned to visit him? What's become of the symbol of Superman in the future? And just why is the future so dangerous for Superman? They warned him away, but now he's determined to help his friends -- even if it means his life!
name: TPB

volume.name: Superman and the Legion of Super-Heroes

description:
1. Döden Väljer Sina Offer  (Batman, Phantom Stranger, James Gordon, Max Lustig, Kaluu / written by Bob Haney : translated from: Brave and the Bold #145)
 
2.  Ace, Läderlappshunden Läderlappen (Batman, Ace the Bathound, Robin, Ace, Bert Bowers, John Wilker, James Gordon / written by Bill Finger : translated from: Batman #92)
 
3. Berättelsen om Kid Killer (Earl "Kid Killer" Mako, Danny Foster  
 
4. En Annan Sorts rättvisa  Läderlappen och Dödingen (Batman, Deadman, Turk Bannion, Achille Lazlo, James Gordon, Gassman / written by Bob Haney : translated from: Brave and the Bold #133)
name: Döden Väljer Sina Offer

description:
1) The Jetsons - The Flying Vacuum Cleaner - 4 pages

2) The Jetsons - Homer's Home - 3 pages

3) The Jetsons - Song Hound - 3 pages

4) The Jetsons - Holdup! - 4 pages

5) The Jetsons - Picnic On Saturn - 3 pages

6) A Fishy Couple - 1 page unrelated text story

7) The Jetsons - Modern Conveniences - 1 page

8) The Jetsons - The Big Smell - 3 pages

9) The Jetsons - The Invisible Box - feat. Sum Toi - 3 pages

Copyright 1972 Hanna Barbera Productions, Inc.
name: The Flying Vacuum Cleaner

description: This book contains newspaper strip reprints from 5/30/42 through 8/15/42 completing the "Yollman" story arc and beginning the Tiger Lily storyline.

As dangerous as she is desirable, Modesty Blaise — former criminal mastermind, now an international adventuress — is a classic newspaper strip icon! In this volume, Modesty must take on a group of killers-for-hire, rescue a scientist, and face off against a highly organised gang of blackmailers! This book also includes a look at the Modesty Blaise phenomenon and all-new story introductions by Peter O'Donnell.

Modesty Blaise, cult creation of best-selling author Peter O'Donnell, is back! The adventures of this all-round bad girl and spy are now collected in a luscious Collectors' Edition paperback library! Thrown into searing hotbeds of intrigue, and up against impossible odds, Modesty Blaise proves once and for all that the female of the species is deadlier than the male. With her trusted right-hand man, Willie Garvin, and the underworld resources of 'The Network' on tap, no job is too big, no threat too great!
name: The Gabriel Set-Up

description:
The night is thick with 1000 ninjas again! Neil Vokes, Jack Herman and Rich Rankin created one of the most enduring indie icons of the 1980s with Eagle! One part supernatural horror and one part ninjitsu action, Eagle is 100% enthralling and guaranteed to take you back to a time when black & white comics were shaking the comic world to its core. Step into the world of Eagle once again and experience the hidden fight against the forces of the supernatural!

The place is Crystal City and you can get killed here for no reason at all.

...is the first sentence in the first issue of Eagle. A perfect setup line to describe the world the next 26 pages begins to introduce. Within the pages of issue 1, Night of 1000 Ninjas!, we meet the protagonist of the series, Richard Eagle - a vigilante whose detective skills are matched by his martial arts abilities and mystical/occult powers - as well as various supporting characters including Lord Kagami, a villain out to destroy Eagle.
name: Night of 1000 Ninjas!

description: In order to heal the wounds in his heart, Eiri Yuki and his vocalist lover, Shuichi, travel to New York to visit the grave of Yuki's first love and tormentor, Yuki Kitagawa. But once there, they make a startling discovering that will change their lives...forever! The eagerly awaited sequel to the shonen-ai smash hit begins right here!
name: Vol. 1

description: After saving two young women, Rushuna and Yajiro are invited to stay at the women's inn--a pleasure palace run by a sassy hostess named Touka Kurenai. But when one of Rushuna's gun is stolen, our busty gun-toting hero is led on a wild chase, which ends in a hot and spectacular mano-a-mano with an even more fiery Touka. Has Rushuna met her match? Or will the heat of battle lead to something more? Kaise-sensei's exhilarating, action-packed manga, filled with beautiful babes, a surprise marriage proposal, and one grueling fight against giant mechanical doll, continues!
name: Vol. 2

description:
The gun-toting blonde bombshell is back. This time Rushuna's peaceful mission is turned topsy-turvy once she meets the most unlikely villian. Nonviolence seems to be more of a state of mind than something that is actually practiced. Will her gun skills ever be put to rest or will her mission remain impossible? Kaise-sensei's exhilarating, action-packed manga doesn't miss a beat on this quest for world peace.

Contents

  • The Unsinkable Rushuna Tendo
  • Of Guns and Swords and Ballooks
  • The Emperor's Envoy
  • The Juttensen Teppa "Gaifu" Aizen
  • Onward To the Mountain of Evil
name: Vol. 3

description:
Rushuna and company finally can take a break after scaling Mount Nabanba. Even in times of peace, Rushuna cannot get a quick minute to think. Mikan sneakingly wanders off to eat a rice ball, but falls into a trap of three shadowy figures. Rushuna and Yajiro must save Mikan without getting killed! Rushuna now must face her most dangerous adversary--herself.

Contents

  • Blind Shot
  • Song of the Himawari
  • Rushuna---Attack!
  • Dance of the Eagle
  • The Juttensen Shinnoshin "Suiro" Hakubi
name: Vol. 4

description:
The golden-haired gunslinger Rushuna continues her journey through a land not her own in order to discover the truth about the past she can't remember, accompanied by the samurai Yajiro and the young balloon master Mikan. Their path has led them to the Imperial Capital--but the Juttensen, elite Imperial fighters pledged to protect the city, bar their way with deadly skill. The trio aren't the only interlopers trying to get into the city--and one mercenary among the attacking rebel forces has good reason to hold a grudge against Yajiro!

Contents

  • Rushuna Arrives At the Imperial Capital!
  • Ferocious Tactics
  • The World's Greatest Spear
  • Samurai Road---The Tiger's Sword
  • Samurai Road---On This Blade I Swear
name: Vol. 5

description:
The adventures of golden-haired gunslinger Rushuna Tendo continue... When Yajiro's blade and an embarrassing picture of Rushuna are stolen, the two set off after the culprit--who turns out to be none other than Rushuna's old master! And after they're surrounded by thermal-targeting death machines commanded by the Iron-Masked Baron himself, Rushuna's "double" also shows up--itching for revenge!

Contents

  • Running Through the Night!
  • Dirty Deeds
  • And That Name Is the Legendary
  • battle At Dawn
  • Golden Rainbow
name: Vol. 6

description:
The truth of Rushuna's past finally comes to light amid impending darkness! The Juttensen and loyalist factions prepared well for the final battle, but they weren't ready for the onslaught the rebels had prepared for them. Traitorous nobles welcome them into the Imperial Capital where the Iron-Masked Baron reveals a weapon capable of harnessing raw energy for the ultimate destructive power. Can the hot gunslinger gang possibly stand against a power great and terrible enough to destroy an entire land?

Contents

  • Bullets Strike Through Bronze
  • Rushuna Tendo: Birth
  • Rushuna Tendo: To Battle
  • Too Hazy To See the Moon
  • The Nightmare Revisited
  • Smile Like A Sunflower
  • Bonus: Steam Queen Competition
name: Vol. 7

description: Join Brothers Stinky and Stan Grosse as they embark on extraordinary--albeit smelly--adventures! From the dense jungle of the boys' imagination where they stumble upon a lost temple (psst: it's in their backyard), to a class trip at the science museum, you'll just have to follow your nose to find out where the boys will end up next. And, you may ask, how can you tell the brothers apart? Stinky is the silent-but-deadly type, while Stan blows 'em out loud and proud!
name: The Good, the Bad and the Gassy

description: When aliens from outer space land on the roof of Stinky and Stan's home, will it be the beginning of the war of the worlds? Nonsense! These aliens worship the Grosse brothers for their farting abilities--the gas that the boys boldly blast causes plants to grow and flowers to bloom. But upon inspection of the boys' room, the aliens are presented with quite a fragrant fright... Hold your nose and hang on for another out-of-this world adventure!
name: Stinky & Stan Blast Off!

description: Stinky and Stan have finally become full-fledged members of the Buzzards and are headed to Spruce Mountain for a camping trip! Aside from enjoying the great outdoors, the boys are charged with the task of earning a variety of achievement patches. But when the boys meet another "troop" looking to collect their own achievement patches, will Stinky and Stan be able to protect themselves? Or, will there be another “Grosse” misunderstanding?
name: Trouble at Twilight Cave

description: Before Ekichi Onizuka would become the "Greatest Teacher in the World," he and Ryuji Danma were members of infamous biker gang, Oni Baku. When not out riding around and getting into trouble, this duo could be found in school, trying to pick up young woman!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi

description: The hilarious second volume to the GTO prequel. Onizuka strikes back in trying to get some hot girl action. Armed with his lame one-liners and his persistence to go from goofy virgin to sexual playboy is a deadly combination. Will he finally make it in the big leagues?
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi

description: Eikichi is the last man standing to make his move on Kaoru. He finally has some alone time with her. Will this be his first? Kaoru has a surprise for him, which he may not like. Meanwhile, the fun doesn’t stop there, Ryuji has set his eyes on a sweet beautiful girl named Ayumi. It seems that Ayumi's past can be the end to Oni-Baku! With eyeopeners, goodies, and surprises, this volume of GTO cannot be missed!
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi

description: Our main man Eikichi is still living the hard knocked life. This time around, an old acquaintance has showed up with a very humiliating request— pay him and bow down. Now, it is up to Eikichi if he will fall to the whims of this bully or go to war! While war is brewing, will Oni-Baku be able to mount up and defend their honor?
name: Vol. 4

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi

description: Makoto's old girlfriend thinks she's pregnant; will Eikichi have to pound some responsibility into him? And when spring break is over and the boys show up for their new school year, the principal has a little surprise--they're being held back! But no worries, that just means it'll be easier for them to score some freshman girls, right?
name: Vol. 5

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi

description: When summer comes to Shonan, Ryuji sees something that just may make him forget Ayumi--the thong-clad bottom of the lovely Nagisa. While Ryuji is taken by the charming girl, Eikichi is distracted by the insane Midnight Angels biker Yasha. The only problem the boys have is...Yasha and Nagisa are one in the same! As her split personality is revealed, they barely have time to save Ryuji from another broken heart--as Yasha and Akutsu, the former leader of Midnight Angels, are plotting to take Oni-Baku down and resurrect the gang to its former glory...
name: Vol. 6

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi

description: Ryuji realizes he's spent four nights with Nagisa but hasn't done the deed...and wonders if he should. Meanwhile, Eikichi takes Nagisa and Ryuji to the beach in an attempt to figure out what turns Nagisa into Yasha, and finds it when Akutsu shows up and snatches her back! Meanwhile, the Tsujido boys learn that Akutsu is after the old Midnight Angel leader's coat, which Oni-Baku happens to have. Will Ryuji get his girl back, and can Oni-Baku stop Midnight Angel from starting a gang war, the likes of which have never been seen before?
name: Vol. 7

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi

description: Eikichi takes Akutsu to meet his hero, Masaki, the founder of Midnight Angel...only Masaki i shigher up than Akutsu ever imagined. Meanwhile, Ryuji is in the hospital hoping his love will again open her eyes. When she does, he's in for a big surprise! And when Katsuyuki feels like punching someone, a punked-out boy on a Steed provides just the opportunity he needs. The time has come for an all-out brawl in this volume of Shonen Junai Gumai!
name: Vol. 8

volume.name: GTO: The Early Years - Shonan Junai Gumi
